ecess appointments when the Senate isn''t in recess is neither rational nor moderate. It''s a raw misuse of executive power by a president whose love of government is his most vulnerable spot with the electorate.', 68723, 0), (485021, 'Every government program needs to be more efficient. Instead of pointing out how other programs can tighten their belts, every program administrator must look inward to save money.', 71175, 0), (485022, 'I have been supporting the European Union, but we are still a work in progress. We have to become more of a United States of Europe. We should talk about electing a president of the E.U., rather than having one selected from the heads of government.', 71248, 0), (485023, 'Barack Obama likes to point to General Motors as the poster child for the job creation success of his economic policies. However, whatever your sentiments about the government''s bailout of General Motors, for every job Barack Obama ''saved-or-created'' in the U.S. there were two jobs off shore.', 75324, 0), (485024, 'I''m not an agent from any government, even if some of you may not believe it. I''m not. I''m a peacemaker.', 68724, 0), (485025, 'I do strongly believe myself that members of the government who sit in the House of Lords should be accountable to the elected House because otherwise there is a democratic deficit, and that is wrong.', 71475, 0), (485026, 'There are an awful lot of people who despise government precisely because it opened the door for common citizenship for people of all races and all natures in the United States.', 73100, 0), (485027, 'Like all good citizens, the elderly and people with disabilities want to eradicate waste and fraud from government, but helping people with special needs meet their basic needs doesn''t fit this description.', 199, 0), (485028, 'It''s tough and it should be tough - it should never be easy to be given millions of pounds to make a drama. The coalition government is doing terrible things to the BBC, but drama will survive even if we end up putting on a play in a backroom of a pub.', 9722, 0), (485029, 'The right of revolution, which tyrants, in mockery, accord to mankind, is no legal right under a government; it is only a natural right to overturn a government.', 2815, 0), (485030, 'The federal government spends millions to run the Postal Service. I could lose your mail for half of that.', 65734, 0), (485031, 'What has been adjudicated and established in the wake of Vietnam and the Civil Rights movement is the ability of the press to basically write or broadcast almost anything about the government. There''s very few restrictions in that way.', 75393, 0), (485032, 'The tenth amendment said the federal government is supposed to only have powers that were explicitly given in the Constitution. I think the federal government''s gone way beyond that. The Constitution never said that you could have a Federal Reserve that would have $2.8 trillion in assets. We''ve gotten out of control.', 68994, 0), (485033, 'The phrase ''perception is reality'' is overused generally. But perception can be reality in monetary policy. The bond market doesn''t act merely on what it sees. It acts on what it expects of the Fed or the government.', 45206, 0), (485034, 'It is only when there is the supervision and critical oversight from the people that the government will be in a position to do an even better job, and employees of government departments will be the true public servants of the people.', 71268, 0), (485035, 'Spreading the wealth punishes success while setting America on course for a greater dependency on government.', 67560, 0), (485036, 'The more people who are dependent on government handouts, the more votes the left can depend on for an ever-expanding welfare state.', 2589, 0), (485037, 'We need an equal opportunity society, one in which government does not see its job as picking winners and losers. Where do you go if you want special favors? Government. Where do you go if you want a tax break? Government. Where do you go if you want a handout? Government. This must stop.', 69478, 0), (485038, 'The government has no business telling an individual what kind of light bulb to buy.', 66573, 0), (485039, 'Just as the Internet drops transaction and collaboration costs in business and government, it also drops the cost of dissent, of rebellion, and even insurrection.', 55391, 0), (485040, 'SpaceX has the potential of saving the U.S. government $1 billion a year. We are opposed to creating an entrenched monopoly with no realistic means for anyone to compete.', 10864, 0), (485041, 'Administrators are there because of the fans and the cricketers to run this game, so credibility of a game, or a board, or even a government for that matter, is important irrespective of what you do. If you are in public life, it is important.', 69228, 0), (485042, 'Healthcare should be between the doctor and the patient. And if the doctor says something needs to be done, the government should guarantee it gets paid for.', 17499, 0), (485043, 'American government is like a train on a track. You have the people on the left shouting you have the people on the right. But the train''s on track. They just keep ploughing ahead. ', 2476, 0), (485044, 'I learnt a lot in government, and I''ve learnt a lot since leaving government. The kind of journey of being in government is that you start at your most popular and least capable, and you end at your most capable and least popular.', 17822, 0), (485045, 'Show me one dictatorship in the world that has not been supported by the United States government or some European governments. It almost doesn''t exist. I think a dictatorship and hegemony are part of the same phenomenon.', 67818, 0), (485046, 'I don''t think that much change comes from economists. I think it comes more from political realities. Probably the two giants of the 20th century, who actually did shift government policy in the U.S. and around the world, were John Maynard Keynes and Milton Friedman. I don''t see anybody in our system who is at that level of influence.', 69148, 0), (485047, 'The majority of Taiwan people cannot accept Taiwan becoming a second Hong Kong, nor can we accept Taiwan becoming a local government of the People''s Republic of China or a Special Administrative Region of China.', 70787, 0), (485048, 'You can''t start with imbalance and end with peace, be that in your own body, in an ecosystem or between a government and its people. What we need to strive for is not perfection, but balance.', 1251, 0), (485049, 'Conservatives believe in smaller government and in the power of the electorate. So I think that we''re less likely to try to use a dramatic forum to warp people''s political views.', 2221, 0), (485050, 'Like many of his fellow skyjackers, 49-year-old Arthur Gates Barkley was motivated by a complicated grievance against the federal government. In 1963, the World War II veteran had been fired as a truck driver for a bakery, after one of his supervisors accused him of harassment.', 71593, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (485051, 'Feeling good about government is like looking on the bright side of any catastrophe. When you quit looking on the bright side, the catastrophe is still there.', 10731, 0), (485052, 'If you ask the government to solve all of your problems, it''s a bit like asking your wife to cook and clean, to raise the children, to hold down a second job to help with the family finances, to keep her parents happy and well and keep your parents happy and well, and to also - to do the lawn and clean the gutters.', 10731, 0), (485053, 'Something that confirms all fears and many conspiracy theories about government is finding out what our elected representatives would put into law if they could.', 10731, 0), (485054, 'I would cap the amount of federal government can spend at 20 percent of the economy. Bring it back to 20 percent or lower. And say, we are not going to spend above that level. Democrats, they want to raise your taxes and spend more and more and turn us into an economy which is no longer driven by the private sector.', 52321, 0), (485055, 'Perhaps religious conscience upsets the designs of those who feel that the highest wisdom and authority comes from government. But from the beginning, this nation trusted in God, not man. Religious liberty is the first freedom in our Constitution.', 52321, 0), (485056, 'I think governments can''t do much.', 5025, 0), (485057, 'Obama might think of himself as one, but he is not a dictator. We are not a banana republic yet. This is not an authoritarian form of government. This is a constitutional republic, and the president doesn''t allow or disallow. The president can''t buy or purchase.', 17531, 0), (485058, 'The best government is that which teaches us to govern ourselves.', 282, 0), (485059, 'Big and oppressive government has long been the enemy of freedom, something black Americans know all too well.', 67555, 0), (485060, 'Government always finds a need for whatever money it gets.', 1727, 0), (485061, 'We need a president who realizes that there''s no government business in show business.', 9137, 0), (485062, 'The U.S. Constitution protects our privacy from the prying eyes of government. It does not, however, protect us from the prying eyes of companies and corporations.', 19485, 0), (485063, 'This country has come to feel the same when Congress is in session as when the baby gets hold of a hammer.', 1122, 0), (485064, 'When people talked about protecting their privacy when I was growing up, they were talking about protecting it from the government. They talked about unreasonable searches and seizures, about keeping the government out of their bedrooms.', 11414, 0), (485065, 'Government is at its worst when you have apathy from its citizens.', 16709, 0), (485066, 'We believe a renewed commitment to limited government will unshackle our economy and create millions of new jobs and opportunities for all people, of every background, to succeed and prosper. Under this approach, the spirit of initiative - not political clout - determines who succeeds.', 66572, 0), (485067, 'President Obama''s reckless defense cuts that are hanging over our cloud, hanging over the horizon could put almost 44,000 jobs at stake right here in Pennsylvania. we are not going to let that happen. You know why? Because No. 1, national defense is the first priority of the federal government.', 66572, 0), (485068, 'When the people become involved in their government, government becomes more accountable, and our society is stronger, more compassionate, and better prepared for the challenges of the future.', 12194, 0), (485069, 'Even if the government spends itself into bankruptcy and the economy still does not recover, Keynesians can always say that it would have worked if only the government had spent more.', 2589, 0), (485070, 'In the inner city, there''s a mentality that the government owes you something. My breakthrough came when I stopped feeling sorry for myself and took responsibility for every part of my life. No more pity parties. I''ve gotta love me more than anybody else loves me.', 47442, 0), (485071, 'Are we still a country that takes risks, that innovates, that believes anything is possible? Or are we a country that is resigned to whatever liberty the government decides to dish out?', 23128, 0), (485072, 'If you''re an old pro, you know how well you''re doing when you''re doing it, and your inner government spanks you if you''re not doing well.', 2216, 0), (485073, 'Nobody is starving on the streets. We''ve always taken care of them. We take care of our own we always have. It is not the government''s responsibility. ', 1793, 0), (485074, 'This is a country for, of, and by the people not for, of, and by the government. If we turn it over to them we cannot complain about what they''re doing because this is a natural course of men and we have to hold their feet to the fire.', 1793, 0), (485075, 'Voters quickly forget what a man says.', 9695, 0), (485076, 'When you decide to get involved in a military operation in a place like Syria, you''ve got to be prepared, as we learned from Iraq and Afghanistan, to become the government, and I''m not sure any country, either the United States or I don''t hear of anyone else, who''s willing to take on that responsibility.', 1749, 0), (485077, 'When the three branches of government have failed to represent the citizenry and the mass of the media has failed to represent the citizenry, then the citizenry better represent the citizenry.', 2221, 0), (485078, 'All government wars are unjust.', 17756, 0), (485079, 'I strive never to forget the real world consequences of my decisions on individuals, businesses and government.', 11622, 0), (485080, 'What is most needed in Darfur is an international peacekeeping and protection presence, and this is what the Sudanese government most wants to avoid.', 17792, 0), (485081, 'Democracy is not so much a form of government as a set of principles.', 1970, 0), (485082, 'If you live in a place that you perceive to be a crowded place, you appreciate government; you see it as this thing that protects you against crime, that keeps order, that makes sure that nobody puts a massage parlor next to your house, that keeps other people''s dogs from pooping on the sidewalk.', 19519, 0), (485083, 'Any government, that is its own judge of, and determines authoritatively for the people, what are its own powers over the people, is an absolute government of course. It has all the powers that it chooses to exercise. There is no other or at least no more accurate definition of a despotism than this.', 2815, 0), (485084, 'It is manifest that the only security against the tyranny of the government lies in forcible resistance to the execution of the injustice; because the injustice will certainly be executed, unless it be forcibly resisted.', 2815, 0), (485085, 'The secret ballot makes a secret government and a secret government is a secret band of robbers and murderers. ', 2815, 0), (485086, 'It is self-evident that no number of men, by conspiring, and calling themselves a government, can acquire any rights whatever over other men, or other men''s property, which they had not before, as individuals.', 2815, 0), (485087, 'There is often, in the affairs of government, more efficiency and wisdom in non-action than in action.', 63147, 0), (485088, 'You don''t pay taxes - they take taxes.', 2171, 0), (485089, 'I have had no contact with the Chinese government. I only work with journalists.', 25121, 0), (485090, 'We''ve supported the U.S. every step of the way. The Philippines was the first government in Asia after September 11, in fact, the night of September 11; it was nighttime for us then. It was daytime here. We were the first government in Asia to come out and say that we''re supporting the U.S.', 70510, 0), (485091, 'It''s hard to get fired from the government. You have to, like, kill people.', 28284, 0), (485092, 'For in reason, all government without the consent of the governed is the very definition of slavery.', 995, 0), (485093, 'In a way, NAFTA is like a scrambled egg. How do you unscramble an egg? The value chains are so interwoven that it would be very difficult to do that. But government policies force us to look for ways to unscramble it.', 68288, 0), (485094, 'The mistake the apartheid government made was they gave the black people nothing, so they had nothing to lose. But now a lot of the former freedom-fighters are big-time capitalists. They''ve been given directorships in every major company. They''re billionaires!', 30001, 0), (485095, 'The most important ways in which I think the Internet will affect the big issue is that it will make it more difficult for government to collect taxes.', 16707, 0), (485096, 'Power must be used, but it must be tempered by soul-searching and the recognition of our human capacity for error. That is the maxim that should inform our approach to every challenge, from reforming state government to engaging in foreign affairs.', 17581, 0), (485097, 'I think the country''s getting disgusted with Washington partly because of the decline of civility in government.', 68665, 0), (485098, 'You have citizens who don''t understand how government works and they''re kind of soured on it. All they do is criticize. They have no idea that they can make things happen.', 10500, 0), (485099, 'We have a complex system of government. You have to teach it to every generation.', 10500, 0), (485100, 'For students, understanding the separate and unique functions of each branch of government can help them understand how different kinds of government officials can help solve different kinds of problems.', 10500, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (485101, 'If there''s anything a public servant hates to do it''s something for the public.', 14120, 0), (485102, 'But I don''t want massive layoffs of anyone - public or private. We are planning on shrinking government through attrition and reform, not through random pink slips.', 73082, 0), (485103, 'Where might is mixed with wit, there is too good an accord in a government.', 1401, 0), (485104, 'I totally accept that it''s a legitimate criticism that when you are involved in the day-to-day scrum of government... that what can get lost is the narrative, the hymn sheet... the song that inspires and lifts people''s sights.', 17720, 0), (485105, 'The healthcare bill not only is a monstrosity in terms of growing the government and cutting out the private sector, the way it was passed was sleazy. Every old Washington trick was used to pass the healthcare bill.', 72137, 0), (485106, 'The soviet people want full-blooded and unconditional democracy.', 41880, 0), (485107, 'Ex-Presidents of the United States get state subsidies. Not so in Russia. You get no government support.', 41880, 0), (485108, 'My fundamental interests are to preserve the good name and standing of this Australian Labor Party and to act in the national interest on behalf of the Australian Government.', 67684, 0), (485109, 'What''s been happening in Iraq, what young Americans wearing flak jackets, helmets and flight suits have done is... created the circumstances under which Iraq can become our closest ally in that part of the world and still have a representative government. And that''s going to be a very good thing considering what''s going on in that neighborhood.', 17647, 0), (485110, 'It is perfectly true that that government is best which governs least. It is equally true that that government is best which provides most.', 3643, 0), (485111, 'I do not intend to dispute in any way the need for defence cuts and the need for government spending cuts in general. I do not share a not in my backyard approach to government spending reductions.', 72775, 0), (485112, 'Poor people cannot rely on the government to come to help you in times of need. You have to get your education. Then nobody can control your destiny.', 15009, 0), (485113, 'We can''t have democracy if we''re having to protect you and our users from the government over stuff we''ve never had a conversation about. We need to know what the parameters are, what kind of surveillance the government is going to do, and how and why.', 19657, 0), (485114, 'I had a lot of friends in high school who said, ''Louie, I don''t care what the government does as long as they leave me alone.'' Well, guess what, when you don''t care what the government does, it does not leave you alone.', 71178, 0), (485115, 'The U.S. economy and workers benefit from a strong, healthy relationship between government and business.', 67475, 0), (485116, 'A corporation''s primary goal is to make money. Government''s primary role is to take a big chunk of that money and give it to others.', 68161, 0), (485117, 'There are three species of government: republican, monarchical, and despotic.', 71516, 0), (485118, 'Washington is a place where politicians don''t know which way is up and taxes don''t know which way is down.', 3158, 0), (485119, 'If we would vote in mass on the more promising ticket, or, if the two are equally bad, would throw out the party that is in, and wait till the next election and then throw out the other party that is in - then, I say, the commercial politician would feel a demand for good government and he would supply it.', 27571, 0), (485120, 'The Soviet government sprouted and grew out of the habits, the psychology, and the condition of the Russian people. It fitted them. They understand it.', 27571, 0), (485121, 'I am constitutionally competent to contest the elections.', 16721, 0), (485122, 'Democracy needs support, and the best support for democracy comes from other democracies.', 16721, 0), (485123, 'To hear some men talk of the government, you would suppose that Congress was the law of gravitation, and kept the planets in their places.', 24952, 0), (485124, 'People like getting what they think is free stuff from government.', 71429, 0), (485125, 'The basic idea that if you increase government spending or you cut people''s taxes that stimulates the economy and lowers the unemployment rate, is a very widely accepted idea. It''s in every economics textbook, that''s what we teach our undergraduates, and I certainly try to teach them the truth.', 71517, 0), (485126, 'It is what we prevent, rather than what we do that counts most in Government.', 62778, 0), (485127, 'Government can contribute to a shared sense of purpose on the part of the citizenry that''s its highest and best application. ', 73333, 0), (485128, 'Our great Republic is a government of laws and not of men. Here, the people rule.', 10283, 0), (485129, 'I have 120 people in my payroll without any government giving me any money. We live off the tickets and the records I sell. That is very unusual.', 68426, 0), (485130, 'We should not have a government program that determines if you''re going to pull the plug on grandma.', 72545, 0), (485131, 'The fight for reform comes down to a simple goal: giving our citizens the confidence that government serves the people first and the people only.', 67356, 0), (485132, 'To me, regardless of who''s in office, the government is strangled by business. And the government''s priorities are dictated by business. I mean, why does America, even after healthcare reform, still not have free universal healthcare? I''m sure it has something to do with the insurance lobby.', 75394, 0), (485133, 'Left to me, the whole purpose of government is for the security of the citizens, like the security of lives and property.', 66760, 0), (485134, 'Socialism means slavery.', 63500, 0), (485135, 'I have long believed taxpayers make better use of their money than the government ever could.', 73794, 0), (485136, 'Increased government spending can provide a temporary stimulus to demand and output but in the longer run higher levels of government spending crowd out private investment or require higher taxes that weaken growth by reducing incentives to save, invest, innovate, and work.', 73923, 0), (485137, 'Freedom only for the members of the government, only for the members of the Party - though they are quite numerous - is no freedom at all.', 8683, 0), (485138, 'The Ethiopian government''s use of the railway from Djibouti to Addis Ababa was, in practice, a hazardous regards transport of arms intended for the Ethiopian forces.', 15968, 0), (485139, 'When government disappears, it''s not as if paradise will take its place. When governments are gone, other interests will take their place.', 16077, 0), (485140, 'Individuals can spend their money more wisely, efficiently and more humanely than can government.', 55271, 0), (485141, 'If children do not understand the Constitution, they cannot understand how our government functions, or what their rights and responsibilities are as citizens of the United States.', 68210, 0), (485142, 'Never did a government commence under auspices so favorable, nor ever was success so complete.', 68738, 0), (485143, 'Financial crises require governments.', 66779, 0), (485144, 'Here''s to democracy. May we get the government we deserve.', 66382, 0), (485145, 'Last, in restaurants you spend a lot of time dealing with people who are very unhappy. Soup has been spilled on their laps, they''ve waited 10 minutes to get their check so they can leave, and you learn how to listen, I think, in a much more proactive way than government does.', 75395, 0), (485146, 'I cannot separate the finances of India from those of England. If the finances of the Indian Government receive any severe and irreparable check, will not the resources of England be called upon to meet the emergency, and to supply the deficiency?', 73404, 0), (485147, 'You can have a revolution wherever you like, except in a government office; even were the world to come to an end, you''d have to destroy the universe first and then government offices.', 15954, 0), (485148, 'A government is not legitimate merely because it exists.', 3797, 0), (485149, 'A government full of Democrats would rather have you be a Republican, and a government full of Republicans would rather have you be a Democrat, than have you oppose both.', 13028, 0), (485150, 'Americans no longer look to government for economic security; rather, they look to their portfolios.', 70535, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (485151, 'As a governor, I am naturally inclined to focus on the domestic side of protecting the United States.', 70535, 0), (485152, 'Too often, Indian tribes are at the mercy of the shifting political winds of State government.', 66768, 0), (485153, 'Sheikh Hasina''s government is one of the best Bangladesh has ever had. She is taking action against fundamentalists. But even she refused to let me return. I don''t think I can ever return home.', 10634, 0), (485154, 'Vetting and verifying information is one thing. Having our government sending out conflicting messages to the American people when conflict can be avoided is another.', 72907, 0), (485155, 'The debt ceiling at some point has to be raised. I don''t think there''s anybody that questions the fact that if we ended up getting in a situation where the U.S. government was sending out IOUs like the state of California did at one point, that ends up creating quite a brand problem for our country.', 71823, 0), (485156, 'Without freedom of the press, there can be no representative government.', 59960, 0), (485157, 'The greater part of the governments on earth may be termed monarchical aristocracies, or hereditary dominions independent of the people.', 75396, 0), (485158, 'But the federal government, our collective government, has responsibilities that none of these other levels of government can fulfill; and chief among these is national defense.', 73807, 0), (485159, 'Neither the George W. Bush nor the Obama administrations volunteered to bail out G.M., Chrysler and other parts of the auto sector. Both subscribed firmly to the longstanding American principle that government should resolutely avoid these kinds of interventions, particularly in the industrial sector.', 75397, 0), (485160, 'God leaves to Man the choice of Forms in Government; and those who constitute one Form, may abrogate it.', 63277, 0), (485161, 'We are a coalition government, and that limits our options in some ways. Privatization happens to be one such area.', 32139, 0), (485162, 'We got government off the backs of the people of India, particularly off the backs of India''s entrepreneurs. We introduced more competition, both internal competition and external competition. We simplified and rationalized the tax system. We made risk-taking much more attractive.', 32139, 0), (485163, 'Whenever the government of the United States shall break up, it will probably be in consequence of a false direction having been given to public opinion.', 66833, 0), (485164, 'Get government out of our way, and let freedom and the spirit of the American people shine through.', 75398, 0), (485165, 'Democracy may not prove in the long run to be as efficient as other forms of government, but it has one saving grace: it allows us to know and say that it isn''t.', 4793, 0), (485166, 'But there will be no justice, there will be no government of the people, by the people, and for the people, as long as the government and its officials permit bribery in any form.', 75399, 0), (485167, 'The Government and the Parliament, even the House of Lords, will consent to a large increase of electors; and men who have not considered the subject fully will imagine they have gained much by the concession.', 14054, 0), (485168, 'The reason the government sells the census as your ticket to getting goodies - rather than as your civic duty - is that distributing goodies is now all the government does.', 71535, 0), (485169, 'A good two years after Hurricane Katrina I remember feeling so devastated and so ignorant that there was so much damage still left. I felt like here I was an American and this is an American city and the government hasn''t done enough and people haven''t given back enough. Everyone forgot and the city was lying in waste.', 73134, 0), (485170, 'Margaret Thatcher was a 20th century visionary who understood the power of individual freedom versus the tyranny of government collectivism. She was a loyal supporter and friend of the United States and her terms as prime minister were marked as the beginning of the resurgence of the economy of the United Kingdom.', 73708, 0), (485171, 'The government should set a goal for a clean environment but not mandate how that goal should be implemented.', 74868, 0), (485172, 'The reason this country continues its drift toward socialism and big nanny government is because too many people vote in the expectation of getting something for nothing, not because they have a concern for what is good for the country.', 75367, 0), (485173, 'People try to live within their income so they can afford to pay taxes to a government that can''t live within its income.', 2423, 0), (485174, 'But let us remember, at the same time, government is sacred, and not to be trifled with.', 45201, 0), (485175, 'The only reason of the institution of civil government; and the only rational ground of submission to it, is the common safety and utility.', 45201, 0), (485176, 'When you have a country that''s been accustomed to government spending at a certain level, it is really hard to ratchet it back.', 75391, 0), (485177, 'There are lots of people depending on the government who are good, honest citizens who have worked all their lives.', 9148, 0), (485178, 'But no one has yet succeeded in reducing the size or scope of the federal government.', 45182, 0), (485179, 'It is not the function of the government to keep the citizen from falling into error it is the function of the citizen to keep the government from falling into error. ', 17686, 0), (485180, 'It is in the country''s best interest that Tony Blair rather than Michael Howard should form the next government.', 17686, 0), (485181, 'Our nation is built on the bedrock principle that governments derive their just powers from the consent of the governed.', 71468, 0), (485182, 'Talk is cheap - except when Congress does it.', 63619, 0), (485183, 'The mistakes made by Congress wouldn''t be 