 skepticism of the powers of government agencies to do good.', 16690, 0), (485194, 'It is bad policy to regulate everything... where things may better regulate themselves and can be better promoted by private exertions but it is no less bad policy to let those things alone which can only be promoted by interfering social power. ', 75401, 0), (485195, 'Today 23 years ago dear Grandmama died. I wonder what she would have thought of a Labour Government.', 68759, 0), (485196, 'Elections are held to delude the populace into believing that they are participating in government.', 72443, 0), (485197, 'I don''t like the idea that the government has so much of a say in things.', 75402, 0), (485198, 'People are constantly applying double standards. Take the United States, for example. Washington wants the whole world to admire the country for its democracy. Then the government sends out its army, in the name of this democracy, and leaves behind the kind of chaos we see in Iraq.', 75403, 0), (485199, 'Every generation has a macabre notion that wars, government prohibition, natural disasters or mankind itself could be the downfall of society and the world as a whole.', 3218, 0), (485200, 'The fact that political ideologies are tangible realities is not a proof of their vitally necessary character. The bubonic plague was an extraordinarily powerful social reality, but no one would have regarded it as vitally necessary.', 878, 0);
