y, but the poor have time.', 28772, 0), (485898, 'I would never wear a look that was all the same designer. I always wear at least one thing that is vintage. I dress according to my mood, and I usually spend money on the basics, like leather jackets, handbags, sweaters and shoes.', 69368, 0), (485899, 'People spend time worrying about things they think they have to have and lose perception of what they do have. You can have all the money and material things you want. If you aren''t here to enjoy them, what good do they do?', 67095, 0), (485900, 'Most of Hollywood is about making money - and I love money, but I don''t make the films thinking about money.', 18666, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (485901, 'In school, my favorite subject was math. That''s where I learned to count money.', 73597, 0), (485902, 'Cricketers have a very short shelf life. On an average, you make money through cricket for five years, but you need to survive for sixty years.', 69702, 0), (485903, 'If our soldiers are not overburdened with money, it is not because they have a distaste for riches; if their lives are not unduly long, it is not because they are disinclined to longevity.', 1026, 0), (485904, 'Why are people unemployed? Because there is no work. Why is there no work? Because people are not buying products and services. Why are people not buying products and services? Because they have no money. Why do people have no money? Because they are unemployed.', 69943, 0), (485905, 'I definitely wanted to earn my freedom. But the primary motivation wasn''t making money, but making an impact.', 72139, 0), (485906, 'Money is just the poor man''s credit card.', 2728, 0), (485907, 'So you think that money is the root of all evil. Have you ever asked what is the root of all money?', 631, 0), (485908, 'Neither a borrower nor a lender be.', 13, 0), (485909, 'The safe way to double your money is to fold it over once and put it in your pocket.', 14120, 0), (485910, 'Pennies do not come from heaven. They have to be earned here on earth.', 1945, 0), (485911, 'The man who won''t loan money isn''t going to have many friends - or need them.', 59443, 0), (485912, 'Run for your life from any man who tells you that money is evil. That sentence is the leper''s bell of an approaching looter.', 631, 0), (485913, 'We have the right as individuals to give away as much of our own money as we please in charity but as members of Congress we have no right to appropriate a dollar of the public money. ', 65656, 0), (485914, 'Criminals are never very amusing. It''s because they''re failures. Those who make real money aren''t counted as criminals. This is a class distinction, not an ethical problem.', 1256, 0), (485915, 'My pride fell with my fortunes.', 13, 0), (485916, 'Friends and acquaintances are the surest passport to fortune.', 1304, 0), (485917, 'I have no money, no resources, no hopes. I am the happiest man alive.', 497, 0), (485918, 'I''m hopeless with money I simply spend what I''ve got. ', 7810, 0), (485919, 'I had some money, I made the best paintings ever. I was completely reclusive, worked a lot, took a lot of drugs. I was awful to people.', 70632, 0), (485920, 'We''ve got to put a lot of money into changing behavior.', 1133, 0), (485921, 'It is not the creation of wealth that is wrong, but the love of money for its own sake.', 1945, 0), (485922, 'Money does not make you happy but it quiets the nerves.', 1160, 0), (485923, 'A man is usually more careful of his money than of his principles.', 24754, 0), (485924, 'But men are so full of greed today, they''ll sell anything for a little piece of money.', 71249, 0), (485925, 'Fame is addictive. Money is addictive. Attention is addictive. But golf is second to none.', 69025, 0), (485926, 'The people who are buying stocks because they''re going up and they don''t know what they do deserve to lose money.', 75467, 0), (485927, 'Because its hard to realize now that that was the end of the great depression, you know. All of a sudden all of this is in front of me and I''m solvent, you know. I''m making some money and I know where my next meal is coming from, and I have a new pair of shoes and that''s it.', 75469, 0), (485928, 'My NFL pension can barely pay my son''s tuition. You know, it''s very little money.', 63699, 0), (485929, 'I did my time for the rape. I paid my money to Las Vegas. I paid my dues.', 11133, 0), (485930, 'While money doesn''t buy love, it puts you in a great bargaining position.', 6093, 0), (485931, 'There''s something so romantic about being broke in New York. You gotta do it. You have to live there once without any money, and then you have to live there when you have money. Let me tell you, of the two, the latter is far better.', 1498, 0), (485932, 'I spent more money on one robe than guys spend in five years.', 66686, 0), (485933, 'Money is worth nothing if it can''t buy you the opportunity to love more.', 588, 0), (485934, 'On privacy issues, it''s just like hundreds of years ago when people said, ''I would rather put my money under my pillow than in a bank.'' But today, banks know how to protect money much better than you do. Today, we may not have the answers to privacy issues, but I believe our young people will come up with the solutions.', 66598, 0), (485935, 'Money is the string with which a sardonic destiny directs the motions of its puppets.', 235, 0), (485936, 'We all need money, but there are degrees of desperation.', 1132, 0), (485937, 'There are necessary evils. Money is an important thing in terms of representing freedom in our world. And now I have a daughter to think about. It''s really the first time I''ve thought about the future and what it could be.', 148, 0), (485938, 'Charter schools are public schools that operate, to a certain extent, outside the system. They have more control over their teachers, curriculum and resources. They also have less money than public schools.', 70981, 0), (485939, 'Money takes wings. The only thing that endures is character.', 63699, 0), (485940, 'But if you want to continue to be slaves of the banks and pay the cost of your own slavery, then let bankers continue to create money and control credit.', 73307, 0), (485941, 'Money can''t buy poverty.', 51806, 0), (485942, 'It will be a great day when our schools have all the money they need, and our air force has to have a bake-sale to buy a bomber.', 22, 0), (485943, 'A savvy entrepreneur will not always look for investment money, first.', 34921, 0), (485944, 'People may take a job for more money, but they often leave it for more recognition.', 14924, 0), (485945, 'When men have money and power they get turned on, sexually. They get horny as hell. Can''t imagine why, though.', 71572, 0), (485946, 'And I think the more money you put in people''s hands, the more they will spend. And if they don''t spend it, they invest it. And investing it is another way of creating jobs. It puts money into mutual funds or other kinds of banks that can go out and make loans, and we need to do that.', 67699, 0), (485947, 'If we command our wealth, we shall be rich and free; if our wealth commands us, we are poor indeed.', 2026, 0), (485948, 'A man who gives his children habits of industry provides for them better than by giving them fortune.', 25969, 0), (485949, 'We are not going to achieve a new world order without paying for it in blood as well as in words and money.', 70874, 0), (485950, 'If you can get some of the devil''s money to use for the Lord''s work, if you have to borrow it, it is all right and carry on the work.', 75470, 0);
