 money for themselves... They wait at the end of my street in their cars. Every time I exit my home, I have company.', 20099, 0), (485962, 'I don''t think there is anything wrong in earning money from the sport you love. If you work hard and get benefits from it, there is no harm. The day you feel that you are not working hard and are only looking at the benefits, that''s where the problem is.', 66892, 0), (485963, 'Not only do unemployment benefits help families who are hurting they also put money into their pockets that they''ll then spend - and their spending will keep other Americans in jobs. ', 66627, 0), (485964, 'There is nothing wrong with making money, but that''s not particularly inspiring.', 66656, 0), (485965, 'One should live between extravagance and meanness. Don''t save money by starving your mind. It is false economy never to take a holiday, or never to spend money for an evening''s amusement or for a useful book.', 4025, 0), (485966, 'I''m enjoying life at my fullest. Sometimes you realize that money isn''t everything.', 67038, 0), (485967, 'Money is like manure, of very little use except it be spread.', 1035, 0), (485968, 'It isn''t enough for you to love money - it''s also necessary that money should love you.', 14120, 0), (485969, 'The process by which banks create money is so simple that the mind is repelled.', 4940, 0), (485970, 'I could have played another year, but I would have been playing for the money, and baseball deserves better than that.', 13197, 0), (485971, 'I don''t think the money people in Hollywood have ever thought I was normal, but I am dedicated to my work and that''s what counts.', 1380, 0), (485972, 'Three groups spend other people''s money: children, thieves, politicians. All three need supervision.', 75471, 0), (485973, 'Money is the seed of money, and the first guinea is sometimes more difficult to acquire than the second million.', 1372, 0), (485974, 'Money is neither my god nor my devil. It is a form of energy that tends to make us more of who we already are, whether it''s greedy or loving.', 583, 0), (485975, 'Money is in some respects life''s fire: it is a very excellent servant, but a terrible master.', 34868, 0), (485976, 'Look, you''re here to see me, and I can''t go on until my dealer is here, and he''s waiting to be paid, so give me some money so I can fix up, and then you''ll get your show.', 22869, 0), (485977, 'Don''t give me any money, don''t give me any people, but give freedom, and I''ll give you a movie that looks gigantic.', 21299, 0), (485978, 'Money tends to make people suspicious, if there''s any money floating around.', 70067, 0), (485979, 'We have one of the highest interest rates in the world, and we owe more money per capita than any other country. All we need is a nail hole in the bottom of the boat and we''re sunk.', 66749, 0), (485980, 'Because A Walk To Remember had come out and it had made money and I got a lot of congratulations at that time as it happens out there.', 75472, 0), (485981, 'I think the situation in Toronto is such that there are funding organizations which make it easy for a film to raise more money than it needs and very often that works against a film.', 75473, 0), (485982, 'Our American friends offer us money, arms, and advice. We take the money, we take the arms, and we decline the advice.', 34585, 0), (485983, 'What have I got? No looks, no money, no education. Just talent.', 67573, 0), (485984, 'More than one-third of Mexicans in the United States own property in Mexico, nearly 80 percent send money home and 25 percent have a spouse in Mexico. Assimilation and becoming an American citizen are not the objective for many of them.', 70127, 0), (485985, 'That is where the power, opportunity, and choice come from-when you have money. Money equals opportunity. There is no question.', 4882, 0), (485986, 'Love is cheap. You can buy it anywhere. Lives are cheap. It''s money that''s dear. You have to work days and sit up nights thinking how to make money.', 21474, 0), (485987, 'The extravagant expenditure of public money is an evil not to be measured by the value of that money to the people who are taxed for it.', 66663, 0), (485988, 'I''ve never chased money. It''s always been about what I can do to motivate and inspire people.', 1776, 0), (485989, 'Other than my foundation - mentoring programs - everything I do is for money.', 385, 0), (485990, 'When you''re making an independent film what you don''t have in time and money you have to make up with creativity and diligence.', 66845, 0), (485991, 'I felt in a lot of instances I was deliberately being put through stress because when you''re a guy who generates money, people have a vested interested in controlling you.', 13006, 0), (485992, 'The ''American Idol'' and ''X Factor'' shows, they''re great shows. But I think I need to make a show like that, directed straight to the hood, to the artists that don''t get the attention, that don''t have the money to make themselves representable.', 15440, 0), (485993, 'I''m free of stress and worries now because if I don''t like something I''m doing, I just find the fun in it instead of being miserable. Let me have fun with the people I work with, let me have fun making money - when I grew up so poor, ya know?', 27596, 0), (485994, 'Now workers should have the right to join unions. But unions should not be forced upon workers. And unions should not have the power to take money our of their members'' paychecks to buy the support of politicians that are favored by the union bosses.', 52321, 0), (485995, 'If you got the money honey I got the time and when you run out of money honey I run out of time.', 16011, 0), (485996, 'My luck at the gambling table was varied; sometimes I was fifty to a hundred dollars ahead, and at other times I had to borrow money from my fellow workmen to settle my room rent and pay for my meals.', 12431, 0), (485997, 'I have too much money invested in sweaters.', 13132, 0), (485998, 'I made more money yesterday than I ever thought I''d make in an entire lifetime. But it''s like somebody''s going to take it all away from me and I''ll be back in Texas, installing them damned irrigation wells. I didn''t like that when I was sixteen. And I know I wouldn''t like it when I''m eighty.', 23263, 0), (485999, 'What we need is more money back in the hands of Americans of any economic standing and so raising taxes right now doesn''t make sense.', 75474, 0), (486000, 'There was a time when a fool and his money were soon parted, but now it happens to everybody.', 69260, 0);
